captions.text: [MUSIC PLAYING]
-Hi.

I'm Brooklyn from
Cute Girls Hairstyles,

and today I'm going
to be teaching you
how to do the nested braid.

It's a selfie hairdo,
so it's like a hairdo
you do on yourself.
And it's really easy and simple.
And let's get started.

So first you want part your hair
so that one side of your hair

has more hair than
the other side.

And then you'll want to
take just a big section

from the very front of the
side that has the most hair.

Then you'll split
it into three parts,

just like you're going
to start a normal braid.

And then you'll just
braid it all the way down.

This is a really good
hairstyle for people

who have bangs
because you can pull

your bangs into this braid,
and it'll be out of your face

all day for whatever
you want to do.

And just keep
braiding really fast.
[MUSIC PLAYING]

Sorry, I'm not quite as
braid ninja as my mom is.

So then you'll just
take a little elastic

that matches your hair color,
and put it in at the very end.

And once it's secure you'll
pull this side loosely
around your head.
You'll want it loose.

You don't want it slicked
back because it looks cute
when it's loose.

And then you'll split it
into another three sections.
So here's the first one.
Here's the second.

And you'll pull the braid
into the middle strand
so that it lays further back.

It looks cuter when
it's like that.
And then you'll just do a braid.

Braid it all the
way down like so.

And then you just take one
of these little rubber bands
and secure it at the bottom.

And then you can go back and
you can pull out the braid

so it's a little bit
bigger and softer looking.
And there you go.
You have your nested braid.

It's nice, easy,
simple, and cute.

And I'll turn for you
all the way around.

Hey, you can go check out mine
and Bailey's new channel--
Brooklyn and Bailey.

We just posted a new book
review, and a room tour,
and all these fun videos.

You can come check it
out at this little box
right here-- this little thingy.

Click it and you can go check
out all those new videos.
And we will see you next week.
Bye.
[MUSIC PLAYING]
